FuncDef: This command displays large scale NAT blocks.
CLIs: lsn-blocks [ inside-router <router-instance> ] [ inside-ip <ip-address> ] [ outside-ip-prefix <ip-prefix/length> ] [ outside-port [ <0> <..> <65535> ] ] [ pool <pool-name> ]

ParaDef.Info: Specifies the router instance name and service ID.
Specifies the IP address in a.b.c.d format.
Specifies the IP prefix. Values-a.b.c.d (host bits must be 0).
Specifies the IP prefix length. Values-1 to 32.
Specifies the pool name, up to 32 characters.
